The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Rajib Ahmed arrested

A STAFF REPORTER

Calcutta: Mohun Bagan defender Rajib Ahmed has been arrested for allegedly harassing a schoolgirl called Taniya Chatterjee and remanded in custody for four days. 

Rajib had apparently been teasing the girl for sometime. On Monday evening, he threw an ignited piece of cloth inside Taniyas room. A complaint was lodged by the girls father, Tridib Chatterjee, with the Behala Police station after which Rajib was arrested. The footballer was produced at the Alipore court on Wednesday. 




